name: Warlizard
description: Disclaimer: I watched this with fascination when it happened, followed it daily, and here's my take on it. I'm not saying that I share the same views as I describe below, only that I think this is what really happened.Ok, imagine you really liked something and girls made fun of you for liking it.Specifically, you were a nerd who liked video games, comic books, sci-fi, and other things of that nature. Over time, game publishers were able to figure out what would really sell spectacularly well and tailored games to the young, male demographic. In a word, you.You still got made fun of, but eh, who cared, you had your games and your books, right?But then girls started coming in, and they wanted to play too. You let them play, but they were mostly in *your* world.Then they started wanting things to change, to suit their styles of play, their way of seeing things, and they pointed out that massively inflated breasts were really kinda shitty for girls, that holding that up as the standard was actively hurting young women.You didn't really care, because hell, it's your world, and hey, titties! But more and more girls were playing these games and the more they played, the more they became a valuable demographic, not just an oddity.More and more, people were writing about games and what better way to represent a new market than talk about things that mattered to girls, written *by* girls.Enter Anita Sarkeesian.She's persuasive and reasonable to begin, but the more she speaks, the more she makes, and you're going nuts watching her shit on the games you love while realizing, *she doesn't like the games at all. She isn't a fan. She's just shitting on them to make money*. Many female developers follow her and before long, she has a real voice, so she makes a kickstarter and money POURS in. She promises to make a ton of videos but it isn't too long before she's talking about how Ms. Pacman is sexist and her criticism shifts from something that might make sense into what you think is giant over-reach.You are mad as fuck now but now she has an army behind her, with both male AND female developers and they're all shitting over your beloved games, but even worse, they've moved from criticism, to change.They're *changing* your games, because they have influence. You see anything they do immediately gobbled up by a fawning press and heralded as the greatest thing ever, as long as it has certain themes, certain... SJW themes....See, you hate what you call a "Social Justice Warrior" and you use the term with utter contempt. Enter Zoe Quinn.She's calls herself a developer, but you know she isn't really, even though you've never coded a line in your life, but she makes a game that's essentially a Choose-Your-Own-Adventure with a focus on feminist issues and its far more of a political statement than a game, so YOU shit over HER game.Everyone rallies around the poor girl but you know she's a fraud, the only reason people are praising her shitty game are blue-haired SJWs and "cucks" as you call them. Those "cucks" are working at Kotaku, IGN, you name it and it sure does seem like they have a cosy relationship with game developers because somehow, they always love games that you think suck. Enter Scorned Boyfriend.He's pissed and writes a massive tell-all about how Zoe was cheating on him with 5 different guys. The guys he names are all ones that have vocally supported her and helped her in her career.Well, you ain't no dummy, you can draw the line from A to B.  You start to mock her for being a slut, people dig up nude photos of her and it confirms everything you knew before.The entire gaming industry has been shitting on you and the games you love because they're trying to impress girls and show how progressive they are.It's all so clear and you have a target.Zoe Quinn.She is the face of everything you hate. She's a loud feminist who cheated on her boyfriend and only got where she is for who she had sex with.Gaming journalists rally around her and defend her, but you and your ilk dig through everything that has ever had her name on it, or the 5 guys her bitter ex named.Patterns emerge and it all becomes clear. SJWs are actively destroying the things you love and it's everywhere.When you try to point it out, you're called sexist, misogynistic, a spoiled entitled brat, and you're treated with the contempt that you felt as a kid.No one will listen to you because they fundamentally believe you are a fucking idiot and just need to do what they say and every new article that comes is shitting on you all over again.But now you have a target, because the publishing industry has been in bed (literally and figuratively) with software developers for years, and with the power of a thousands autists, you can "prove" it.And that, my friend, is Gamergate.I didn't bother going over the whole Hugo controversy, the Puppies, and a thousand other minor skirmishes, but you get the idea. Hope this helps.EDIT: BTW, the game Zoe made was called Depression Quest and the idea was that although many options were seemingly available in your Choose-Your-Own adventure, the ones that would help you get over depression were grayed out. Back when this came out I thought it would be hilarious to make a "Repression Quest" where you were a huge chad and the only options that would help you become progressive would be grayed out but then I figured I didn't want to poke that hornet's nest.

name: Warlizard
description: Wait, don't go, it's really simple. It’s a large language model, self-hosted on your own rig. You grab a GGUF file—think distilled neural net weights, quantized to the nth degree, like Q4_K_M with 4-bit precision or Q8_0 with 8-bit integer ops, packed tight with GGML optimizations for minimal memory footprint. Snag it off Hugging Face, maybe a 7B parameter model, 7 billion weights, fits in about 4-6GB of VRAM if you’re lucky. Then you compile llama.cpp—straight C++ inference engine, leverages SIMD instructions, single instruction multiple data, for parallel crunching. Point it at the GGUF, and it’s live, no cloud, no nonsense.Hardware’s key. You need a beefy GPU—say an NVIDIA RTX 4090 with 24GB GDDR6X VRAM, tensor cores screaming at 16-bit float precision, pushing 30 tokens per second on a 13B model. CPU fallback’s doable, Intel i9-13900K with 24 cores, 32 threads, AVX-512 support for vectorized math, but it’ll crawl at 5 tokens per second tops. RAM’s non-negotiable—64GB DDR5 at 5600 MT/s, because context spills into system memory past 8k tokens. Storage? NVMe SSD, Samsung 990 Pro, 2TB, 7450MB/s read, keep those weights streaming.Settings are a playground. Temperature’s a float, 0.65 for tight coherence, 1.8 if you want it spitting chaotic embeddings. Context length—4096 tokens, 4k word fragments, needs 16GB VRAM or it swaps to RAM and stutters. Tokenization’s baked into the GGUF, BPE algo, byte pair encoding, splits text into subword units, 50k vocab size typical. Tuning? LoRA’s your ticket—low-rank adaptation, slap a 16-rank delta on the weight matrix, fine-tune on a 3080 Ti in half a day if you’ve got the dataset.Crazy thought—could you cram it on a Raspberry Pi 5? 8GB LPDDR4X, ARM Cortex-A76, no CUDA, so you’re stuck with CPU inference. Maybe a 1B parameter model, Q2 quantization, 2-bit weights, 500MB footprint. Chugs at 1 token per second if the thermals don’t throttle it to death. Overclock it, liquid cool it, who knows? I’d benchmark it just to see the bus bandwidth choke. Stock’s fine for most, though—13B on a 3090, call it a day....Ladies?
